CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 20, 1946, pg. 1, reads: "...[ill.] Lucky Veterans and their families moved into the new [...] at McKinley Park Monday afternoon, after a colorful celebration attended by Mayor David L. Lawrence, Housing Administrator [...] Klein, and a number of other city officials. These homes were the first of the 750 veterans' temporary housing unites being constructed throughout the city to be readied for occupancy.  The photos, left to right,..Mrs. Nelson signs for her new furniture in next photo...- Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Mrs. Bishop Nelson Jr., signing for new furniture with man looking on, standing in housing unit in McKinley Park
